<HEAD>Fashion Emergency: Dodgers' Hero Ready To Go But Not All Dressed
Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   World Series hero Orel Hershiser had his bags
packed and was ready to hit the talk show circuit when he realized
his wardrobe was limited to Dodger blue. The answer: a fashion
consultant, of course.
   ``It was a fashion emergency,'' said Marti Devore of the Sy
Devore clothing stores.
   After a call from the Los Angeles Dodgers' ace pitcher, Devore
enlisted an army of personal shoppers from the Best Dressed company
to go on a buying spree.
   Hershiser, who didn't take part in the buying binge, packed an
extra bag with the new clothes.
   Among his new purchases were a double-breasted gray suit and a
black herringbone jacket, she said.
   Hershiser won the first and fifth games of the 1988 World Series
as the Dodgers beat the Oakland Athletics four games to one in the
best-of-seven series. He was named the most valuable player of both
the Series and the National League Championship Playoffs.
