<HEAD>Four From Correctional Facility Killed In Truck-Van Collision</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A van taking youths from a juvenile jail
to a movie skidded on an icy highway and collided with a semitruck,
killing four people and injuring 11 others.
   The van from the Minnesota Correctional Facility was carrying 12
youths, ages 15 to 18, and two adult companions to a movie in
Alexandria as a reward for good behavior when the crash occurred
Thursday evening on Interstate 94.
   Three youths and one adult staff member were killed, authorities
said. The victims' identities were being withheld until relatives
had been notified.
   Less than an inch of snow had fallen on roads, a State Patrol
dispatcher said.
   Three people were listed in critical condition, said hospital
spokeswoman Jane Vare, who added that she did not know the
conditions of the other patients.
  
