<HEAD>Snowy Midwest; Rain from Plains into South</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell in the upper Midwest today, and thunderstorms ranged
from the southern Plains into the Tennessee Valley.
   Snow advisories were posted for as much as 3 inches of snow in
northern Wisconsin and winter storm watches were issued for snow and
gusty winds in northern Michigan. Snow also fell in sections of
Minnesota and North Dakota.
   Showers and thunderstorms ranged from northeast Texas to
southeastern Oklahoma, Arkansas, Tennessee and Kentucky. Rain spread
across Indiana, Ohio the lower Great Lakes region and lower Michigan.
   Thunderstorms also were scattered across southeast Florida and
rain fell in southeastern Georgia and South Carolina.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from
central and eastern Texas to Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, the
Florida Panhandle and eastern Tennessee; rain showers from New
England to the northern Appalachians and lower Great Lakes; and snow
showers over northern Michigan.
   Highs were forecast in the 30s from northern Michigan to much of
Wisconsin, the upper Mississippi Valley, the Dakotas and Montana;
40s to 50s from New England into the Great Lakes, central Plains and
Northwest; 80s in Florida, the Gulf Coast region, southern Texas,
and from southern Arizona to southeast and east central California;
and in the 60s and 70s across most of the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 11
degrees at Glasgow, Mont., to 79 at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 57 cloudy; Boston 39 fair; Buffalo 50 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C., 59 fair; Cincinnati 57 windy; Cleveland 50
showers; Miami 74 fair; New York 45 fair; Philadelphia 41 fair;
Pittsburgh 48 cloudy; Portland, Maine 31 fair; Washington 44 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 23 snow; Chicago 37 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 68
partly cloudy; Denver 34 fair; Des Moines 31 windy; Indianapolis 44
windy; Kansas City 35 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 29 snow; Nashville
58 rain; New Orleans 69 fair; St. Louis 45 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 53 windy; Anchorage 31 cloudy; Las Vegas 69
partly cloudy; Los Angeles 61 cloudy; Phoenix 73 fair; Salt Lake
City 46 partly cloudy; San Diego 63 cloudy; San Francisco 54 fair;
Seattle 43 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 41 partly cloudy; Toronto 45 cloudy.
