<HEAD>Vietnamese Floods Kill 27, Damage Homes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Floods caused by heavy rains have killed
27 people and damaged thousands of houses in northern Vietnam, Radio
Hanoi said Friday.
   The broadcast, monitored in Bangkok, said the deaths came in
floods in Nghe Tinh province Oct. 10-18. It also said 5,401 houses
were damaged and thousands of acres of crops flooded.
