<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Greece-Parade,0111</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Greece Remembers War With Military Parade</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALONICA, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers and veterans marched past
President Christos Sartzetakis on Friday at a military parade on a
national holiday marking Greece's entry into World War II.
   Disabled veterans of Greece's 1940-41 campaign against Italian
forces in Albania led the march in this northern city. They were
followed by armed forces and police units, tanks, artillery and
Greek-made personnel carriers.
   The holiday marks the day in 1940 when Greek Premier Ioannis
Metaxas rejected an Italian ultimatum to surrender and entered World
War II on the Allied side. Greece surrendered in April 1941 when
Nazi troops invaded through Bulgaria.
