<HEAD>Philadelphia Daily News Backs Dukakis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Philadelphia Daily News endorsed Democrat
Michael Dukakis for president Friday, saying the Massachusetts
governor may lack excitement but Republican George Bush ``has no
character.''
   ``Michael Dukakis hasn't sold his soul,'' said the newspaper, one
of the city's two major dailies. ``He may not be exciting or
visionary, but he will do better on Central America, the defense
budget, Star Wars, issues involving human freedom (the ones that get
labeled `liberal' or `women's issues') and the Supreme Court, where
appointments are inevitable very soon.
   ``That's enough. We endorse Dukakis.''
   The paper said it ``could have endorsed the 1979-80 George
Bush,'' but ``not this one, not the guy who takes the lowest road
possible, who pretends, despite all the evidence, that J. Danforth
Quayle is not a callow moron, who thinks the CIA is more patriotic
than the ACLU, who is willing to play to any nasty nativist
electoral strain he can find, not the man who determines what he
believes by the polls. That man has no character.''
