<HEAD>New York Post Says Bush Will Lead in Right Direction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The New York Post endorsed George Bush for
president on Friday, calling the Republican nominee ``a champion of
peace through strength, a believer in lower taxes and a free-market
economy.''
   It said its ``chief reason for backing Bush is that _ abroad and
at home, in foreign policy and in domestic affairs _ he will lead
the nation in the right direction.''
   The newspaper called Democrat Michael Dukakis ``a man of honor,
integrity and experience'' who has run ``a dignified and spirited
campaign.''
   ``But he is wedded to the liberal agenda of the 1960s,'' the
paper said. ``To deal with the challenges of the future, Dukakis'
instinct is to turn to the solutions of the past.''
   ``The only aspect of the Bush candidacy that gave us pause was
the presence on the Republican ticket of Sen. Dan Quayle,'' the Post
said, but it added that the vice presidential nominee ``has been
maligned way beyond his personal failings'' and ``is by no means as
poor a choice as has been claimed.''
