<HEAD>Bush Sees Real Spin Control</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Political Rdp Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush got a
first-hand look at ``spin'' doctoring during a demonstration Friday
of police driving techniques at the California Highway Patrol
Academy.
   Watching patrol officers execute high-speed automobile drills and
controlled spins that filled the air with the smoke of burning
rubber, the Republican candidate remarked on how similar it was to
what he was doing.
   ``It's a demonstration where people drive around obstacles at
high speeds trying to avoid cracking up,'' he said.
