<HEAD>Boy Confesses to Releases Brake on Boxcar That Killed Man</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOVELAND, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A boy has confessed to releasing the
brakes on a boxcar that ran over and killed a railroad worker,
police said.
   Detective Sgt. John Teeples said the boy was under age 10 and
would not be charged.
   On Oct. 17, the empty boxcar rolled about a mile before it struck
a Burlington Northern work truck. The boxcar and truck then ran over
Kevin Evenstad, 35, of Fort Collins, as he worked on tracks.
   An investigation by Burlington Northern and police found that one
of six children ``released the brake, not understanding the
consequences.''
   A Federal Railroad Administration investigator said the lever
disengaged by the boy works similarly to a car's emergency brake.
   Attorneys for Evenstad's widow said they plan to file a civil
suit against the railroad.

