<1ST_LINE>s i BC-Charles-Quotes ADV06   10-28 0399</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Charles-Quotes, ADV 06,0414</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>$Adv06</NOTE>
<NOTE>For Release Sunday, Nov. 6, and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>Quotations of Prince Charles</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Charles at 40, b0784-b0785</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is some of what Prince Charles has had to say
on various issues in Britain:
   _On the plight of the unemployed, February, 1985: ``It is only
when you visit these areas, as I do from time to time, that you
begin to wonder how it is possible that people are able to live in
such inhuman conditions.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On London's changing skyline, December, 1987: ``You have to give
this much to the Luftwaffe _ when it knocked down our buildings (in
World War II) it didn't replace them with anything more offensive
than rubble. We did that.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On urban renewal problems, July, 1987: ``This is one of my rare
opportunities to stir things up, to throw a proverbial royal brick
through the plate glass of pompous and professional pride, and jump
feet first into the spaghetti bolognaise of red tape which covers
the country from one end to the other.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On TV violence, September, 1988: ``If, as parents, you complain
that a diet of freely available and insensate violence is likely to
influence the way some people behave and relate to others, then you
are told there is absolutely no proof that violence on TV has any
effect on people's behavior. But that, as we all know, is palpable
nonsense.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On the ozone layer in the environment, February, 1988: ``We are
always told that it is not scientifically proved, but I, personally,
as I have become older and more autocratic, have banned the use of
aerosols in my household.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On charity rock concerts, September, 1985: ``If only I could
sing properly and squeeze myself into denims, I might achieve more.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On his marriage to Princess Diana, 12 years his junior, October,
1985: ``I'm sure it must be absolute hell living with an ancient old
thing like me. ... I trust she'll keep me reasonably young in some
aspects.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   _On getting involved in issues, December, 1987: ``It would be
much easier to lead a quieter life. I don't need to do this, but I
feel strongly about a lot of these things and I cannot do nothing
about it. If people would rather I did nothing I will go off
somewhere else.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, Nov. 6</NOTE>
</DOC>
