<NOTE>For Release Sunday, Nov. 6, and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>Significant Dates in Life of Prince Charles</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-Charles at 40, b0884-b0785</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Significant dates in the life of Prince Charles:
   Nov. 14, 1948 _ Born at Buckingham Palace.
   Feb. 6, 1952 _ Becomes heir apparent and Duke of Cornwall when
his grandfather, King George VI, dies and his mother becomes Queen
Elizabeth II.
   Jan. 28, 1957 _ Starts junior school as first royal heir to be
educated in a classroom.
   July 26, 1958 _ Created Prince of Wales.
   Nov. 14, 1966 _ 18th birthday makes him eligible to accede to the
throne in his own right.
   October, 1967 _ Enters Trinity College, Cambridge, to study
archaeology, anthropology, and history.
   July 1, 1969 _ Formal investiture as Prince of Wales at
Caernarvon Castle.
   March 1971-December 1976 _ Serves in the Royal Air Force and
Royal Navy.
   July 29, 1981 _ Marries Lady Diana Spencer in St. Paul's
Cathedral, London.
   June 21, 1982 _ Birth of first son, Prince William.
   Sept. 15, 1984 _ Birth of second son, Prince Henry.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, Nov. 6</NOTE>
