<HEAD>Dollar Closes Up Against Yen, Market Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar edged up today against the Japanese
yen, while share prices gained marginally.
   The dollar closed at 126.08 yen, up 0.18 yen from from Thursday's
close of 125.90 yen. Opening at 126.10 yen, the currency was traded
within a range of 125.90 yen to 126.30 yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, a 102.31-point
winner Thursday, added another 18.42 points, or 0.06 percent, to
finish trading at 27,741.34.
