<2ND_LINE>BC-British Stocks,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Up Slightly</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rose slightly Friday as worries about
Wall Street and the close of a two-week trading account curtailed
volume and interest in speculative moves.
   Traders said the underlying tone of the market remained firm,
however, after Thursday's surprise narrowing of the British trade
deficit.
   The improved trade figures and a steady pound should provide
support for British equities in the near term, even if New York
share prices take a dive, some dealers said.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was up 2.5
points, or 0.1 percent, at 1,854.6 at midday.
   Volume was a light 262.4 million shares, down from 315.9 million
shares traded by the same time Thursday.
</TEXT>
