<1ST_LINE>d f BC-Times-Cable     10-28 0112</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Times-Cable,0119</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New York Times Co. to Divest Cable TV System</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The New York Times Co. has decided to divest its
cable television system, NYT Cable TV, the diversified
communications company said Friday.
   Arthur Ochs Sulzberger, chairman and chief executive officer,
said in a statement the divestiture was part of the company's
strategy to focus on its other core businesses.
   The company retained First Boston Corp. as adviser to sell the
cable system, a pay-per-view operation purchased seven years ago.
Since then it has grown from 72,000 subscribers to approximately
160,000.
   The New York Times Co. also has interests in newspapers,
magazines, television, radio and forest products.
</TEXT>
