<1ST_LINE>r f BC-BoeingOrder     10-28 0104</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Boeing Order,0109</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Olympic Airways Signs Agreement For Three Boeing 767s</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Olympic Airways will buy three Boeing
767-200s jetliners for a total of $180 million, the airline
announced Friday.
   Under an agreement signed Thursday, Boeing will deliver the
wide-bodied jetliners in early 1990, the announcement said.
   Olympic said it chose the Boeings in July over the European-made
Airbus 300 and 310 because a 767 costs $48 million less than an
Airbus.
   The Greek airline also signed an agreement to fit the aircraft
with Pratt & Whitney jet engines rather than the General Electic
turbofans normally used on Boeing aircraft.
</TEXT>
