<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Aetna     10-28 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Aetna,0207</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Earnings Drop In 3rd Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Aetna Life & Casualty said Friday that its
third quarter earnings fell 7 percent, citing a decline in results
from personal, commercial property and group insurance.
   Aetna said it earned $235 million, or $2.07 a share, in the third
quarter compared with $254 million, or $2.21 a share, in the same
period in 1987.
   The company's operating earnings also fell, by 17 percent, to
$190 million from $231 million in 1987.
   Third-quarter revenue slipped 1.9 percent to $5.67 billion from
$5.78 billion.
   ``Personal and commercial-property results were down from last
year, along with group insurance results,'' said James T. Lynn,
Aetna chairman.
   For the first nine months, the company's net income was $503
million, or $4.40 a share, down 30 percent compared to $723 million,
or $6.24 a share, for the same period last year.
   Operating income in the same period was $471 million, down 26
percent compared to $639 million last year.
   Nine-month revenue rose 9.8 percent to $17.97 billion from $16.44
billion.
   Aetna, based in Hartford, said its assets as of Sept. 30 totalled
$77 billion, 5 percent more than last year.
</TEXT>
